  "description": "Exegetical theology research skills for Pi",
  "readme": "# Theology Pi Plugin\r\n\r\nPi package port of [`theology-claude-plugin`](https://github.com/fingerskier/theology-claude-plugin).\r\n\r\nProvides Agent Skills for rigorous, multi-perspective Biblical exegesis.\r\n\r\n## Install\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npi install npm:@fingerskier/pi-theology\r\n# local workspace clone\r\npi install ./packages/pi-theology\r\n# one run only\r\npi -e npm:@fingerskier/pi-theology\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Skills\r\n\r\n- `/skill:historian` \u2014 historical and cultural background\r\n- `/skill:linguist` \u2014 Hebrew, Greek, Aramaic linguistic analysis\r\n- `/skill:author` \u2014 literary analysis\r\n- `/skill:theologian` \u2014 theological themes and doctrines\r\n- `/skill:disciple` \u2014 hermeneutical/canonical analysis\r\n- `/skill:shepherd` \u2014 practical application\r\n- `/skill:research` \u2014 full exegetical analysis\r\n\r\nNo extension or external runtime is required.\r\n",
